sql:
SELECT model_number
FROM battery_packs
WHERE status = 'In Use';

SELECT summary
FROM test_reports
WHERE report_id = 1;

SELECT name
FROM engineers
WHERE engineer_id IN (SELECT created_by FROM test_conditions);

external_knowledge:
- The cumulative charge capacity can be thought of as the total amount of charge that a battery pack has accumulated over its test cycles;
- A higher average cumulative charge capacity indicates a battery pack's ability to hold more charge over time;
- The ranking of battery packs based on their average cumulative charge capacity can help identify the most reliable or efficient battery packs in the testing environment.

sql:
SELECT AVG(voltage_nominal_V) AS average_nominal_voltage
FROM battery_packs
WHERE status = 'Under Test';

SELECT summary
FROM test_reports
WHERE test_condition_id = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT e.name
FROM engineers e
WHERE e.engineer_id IN (
  SELECT tr.created_by
  FROM test_results tr
);

SELECT MAX(temperature) AS max_temperature
FROM data_logs
WHERE cycle_index = 0;

SELECT e.name
FROM engineers e
JOIN test_cycles tc ON e.engineer_id = tc.created_by;

SELECT manufacturer
FROM battery_packs
WHERE pack_id = 0;

SELECT cycle_index
FROM test_cycles
WHERE charge_capacity = (SELECT MAX(charge_capacity) FROM test_cycles);

SELECT DISTINCT e.name
FROM engineers AS e
JOIN test_cycles AS tc ON e.engineer_id = tc.created_by;

external_knowledge:
- The term 'operational testing stations' implies that the testing stations are currently in use and fully functional; 
- The 'most recent test cycles' refer to the test cycles with the highest rank based on the test time in descending order; 
- The test time is measured in seconds and a test time greater than 10000 seconds is considered long.
